Document: StandardMaterial3D
Path: godot/classes/class_standardmaterial3d.rst
Summary: StandardMaterial3D uses separate textures for ambient occlusion, roughness, and metallic maps while inheriting properties from BaseMaterial3D.

StandardMaterial3D's properties are inherited from BaseMaterial3D. This material type uses separate textures for ambient occlusion, roughness, and metallic maps. To use a single ORM map for all three textures, use an ORMMaterial3D instead. Note: ORMMaterial3D combines ambient occlusion, roughness, and metallic information into a single texture map.
